'''Vivian Inez Archibald''' [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (born 1 February 1945<ref>{{cite web|title=BIOGRAPHY|url=http://www.legco.gov.vg/spawpdfs/Microsoft%20Word%20-%20BIOGRAPHY-Hon.%20V.pdf|website=Legislative Council of the Virgin Islands|accessdate=25 February 2016}}</ref>) is a [[British Virgin Islands|British Virgin Islander]] [[politician]] and [[businesswoman]] who has served as the [[Deputy Governor of the British Virgin Islands]] since September 2008.<ref name=govbvi>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Inez Archibald Appointed Next Deputy Governor|url=http://216.197.123.192/Newsroom/tabid/106/articleType/ArticleView/articleId/89/Inez-Archibald-Appointed-Next-Deputy-Governor.aspx|work=[[Government of the British Virgin Islands]]|publisher=|date=2008-08-21|accessdate=2014-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503204320/http://216.197.123.192/Newsroom/tabid/106/articleType/ArticleView/articleId/89/Inez-Archibald-Appointed-Next-Deputy-Governor.aspx|archive-date=3 May 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=govbvi2>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Mrs. V. Inez Archibald, Function: Deputy Governor|url=http://www.bvi.gov.vg/bio/mrs-v-inez-archibald|work=[[Government of the British Virgin Islands]]|publisher=|date=|accessdate=2014-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503152755/http://www.bvi.gov.vg/bio/mrs-v-inez-archibald|archive-date=3 May 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 21 August 2008, [[Meg Munn]], who held the British ministerial portfolio for the [[British Overseas Territories|Overseas Territories]] at the time, instructed the [[Governor of the British Virgin Islands]] to appoint Archibald as Deputy Governor.<ref name=govbvi/> Inez Archibald took office as the British Virgin Islands' Deputy Governor on 15 September 2008.<ref name=govbvi/>

Archibald holds a bachelor's degree in economics and [[business administration]] from [[Rollins College]].<ref name=govbvi2/> She also received a [[master's degree]] in religion from [[Stetson University]] and a second master's degree in [[divinity]] from [[Emory University]].<ref name=govbvi2/>

Archibald's husband of forty-eight years, prominent British Virgin Islands lawyer [[Joseph Archibald]], died on 3 April 2014.<ref name=kittsobserver>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Son Of The Soil Dr. Joseph S. Archibald, QC Dies|url=http://www.thestkittsnevisobserver.com/2014/03/28/son-of-the-soil-dies.html|work=[[The St. Kitts-Nevis Observer]]|publisher=|date=2014-04-04|accessdate=2014-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407142719/http://www.thestkittsnevisobserver.com/2014/03/28/son-of-the-soil-dies.html|archive-date=7 April 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=bviplatinum>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Hundreds Bid Farewell To Dr. Joseph S. Archibald, QC   |url=http://www.bviplatinum.com/news.php?articleId=1398553826 |work=[[BVI Platinum]] |publisher= |date=2014-04-26 |accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref> They had three daughters.<ref name=bviplatinum/>

Archibald was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in the 2015 New Year Honours.

